OL,6,FAs Motin returned to court to be
OL,7,Fsentenced, Mr Justice Andrew Baker
OL,8,Frejected Motin's account of what
OL,9,Fhappened as "highly implausible".
OL,11,FHe ruled that Motin failed to keep a
OL,12,Fproper lookout, which amounted to a
OL,13,F"wholesale failure of his duty" for an
OL,14,Fextended period of time.
OL,16,FThe judge said Motin's account was
OL,17,F"extremely problematic", "improbable",
OL,18,F"extremely implausible" and "even
OL,19,Fworse" than the prosecution's version
OL,20,Fof events.
